      <Value><![CDATA[<p><strong><span class="lead">Advertising your Vacancies at QMU</span><br /></strong></p>
<p>The most effective way to reach our students and graduates is to register with <a rel="noopener" href="https://employers.studentcentral.qmu.ac.uk/" target="_blank" title="Student Central">Student Central</a>. Through this you can advertise graduate jobs, internships, vacation work, part-time work and volunteering opportunities. You can add, change or delete your vacancies whenever you need to and the system will send automatic emails to students who have expressed interest in your area of work.</p>
<p>If you are interested in advertising a vacancy with us please refer to our <a href="/{localLink:umb://document/3ac4c1f2fdf64be19297f0f2694aa5a2}" title="Employers' Code of Practice - QMU Careers &amp; Employability (QMUCE)">Employer's Code of Practice</a><a href="/{localLink:umb://media/ffb19320708344298c7352fe17ffe838}" title="Employer Code Of Conduct 2015"></a>.</p>
<p><strong><span class="lead">Careers Events and Jobs Fairs</span><br /></strong></p>
<p>Throughout the academic year we deliver and host a number of careers events including our annual <a data-id="3564" href="/{localLink:umb://document/67abc1d7cc8d443084ceea2940bee04d}" title="Volunteering and Recruitment Fairs">Recruitment Fair</a>. These events give you the opportunity to meet and assess potential candidates for employment. They also give you the chance to raise your profile within Queen Margaret University. Subject to availability, we can, at your request, book space for you on campus to give a presentation or set up a stall.</p>
<p>Our September Careers and Recruitment Fairs have now passed for this year. You can email <a href="mailto:careers@qmu.ac.uk">careers@qmu.ac.uk</a> to be added to the mailing list when bookings go live for our September 2024 Fairs.</p>
<p>We will be hosting a Nursing, Health and Social Care Careers Fair in February 2024. For further information about this, please email <a href="mailto:careers@qmu.ac.uk">careers@qmu.ac.uk</a> </p>
<p><strong><span class="lead">Sponsorship</span><br /></strong></p>
<p>You can bring yourself to the attention of all QMU students by sponsoring events such as our Recruitment Fair and being featured in our publications and online activities.</p>
<p>If you would like to be a sponsor or be involved with our activities in any way please <a rel="noopener" href="mailto:careers@qmu.ac.uk" target="_blank" title="Contact QMU Careers and Employability Team">contact us</a>.</p>
<p><strong><span class="lead">Mentor a Student</span><br /></strong></p>
<p>Our <a data-id="3565" href="/{localLink:umb://document/8fef364b82f54b918f588c8fa4d1c7db}" title="Become a Mentor">Employer Mentoring Programme</a> provides free training in how to be a mentor and the rewarding experience of helping a student gain insight and skills related to your field of work.</p>]]></Value>
